            </div>
            <h2 class="text-[#1b140e] text-[22px] font-bold leading-tight tracking-[-0.015em] px-4 pb-3 pt-5">Introduction</h2>
            <p class="text-[#1b140e] text-base font-normal leading-normal pb-3 pt-1 px-4">
              Start with an emotionally engaging introduction. Use storytelling to connect adopters with the pet's personality and background. For example, instead of saying 'This
              is Max,' try 'Meet Max, a playful Labrador with a heartwarming story of resilience.'
            </p>
            <h2 class="text-[#1b140e] text-[22px] font-bold leading-tight tracking-[-0.015em] px-4 pb-3 pt-5">Photography</h2>
            <p class="text-[#1b140e] text-base font-normal leading-normal pb-3 pt-1 px-4">
              Use high-quality photos that capture the pet's personality. Show them in various poses and settings to highlight their unique traits. Avoid blurry or poorly lit
              images. Consider professional photography for the best results.
            </p>
            <div class="flex w-full grow bg-[#fcfaf8] @container p-4">
              <div class="w-full gap-1 overflow-hidden bg-[#fcfaf8] @[480px]:gap-2 aspect-[3/2] rounded-xl grid grid-cols-[2fr_1fr_1fr]">
