            <h2 class="text-[#1b140e] text-[22px] font-bold leading-tight tracking-[-0.015em] px-4 pb-3 pt-5">Descriptions</h2>
            <p class="text-[#1b140e] text-base font-normal leading-normal pb-3 pt-1 px-4">
              Write personalized and evocative descriptions. Focus on the adopter's experience and the pet's unique qualities. Instead of listing facts, describe how the pet will
              enrich their life. For example, 'Max isn't just a dog; he's a loyal companion ready to fill your days with joy and adventure.'
            </p>
            <h2 class="text-[#1b140e] text-[22px] font-bold leading-tight tracking-[-0.015em] px-4 pb-3 pt-5">Emotional Trigger Words</h2>
            <p class="text-[#1b140e] text-base font-normal leading-normal pb-3 pt-1 px-4">
              Incorporate emotional trigger words to create a stronger connection. Words like 'loving,' 'playful,' 'loyal,' 'gentle,' and 'adventurous' can evoke positive emotions
              and make the pet more appealing. Use these words thoughtfully to accurately reflect the pet's personality.
            </p>
